doc.previous: East Germany tried to establish its own airline in 1955 using the Lufthansa name but this resulted in a legal dispute with West Germany where Lufthansa was operating East Germany instead established Interflug as its national airline in 1963 which coincided with the East German Lufthansa being shut down 21
doc.after: In 1958 Lufthansa ordered four Boeing 707s and started jet flights from Frankfurt to New York City in March 1960 Boeing 720Bs were later bought to back up the 707 fleet In February 1961 Far East routes were extended beyond Bangkok Thailand to Hong Kong and Tokyo Lagos Nigeria and Johannesburg South Africa were added in 1962
